original_title: Manhattan: Marble Hill Avenue - Fort Charles Place
text:
Marble Hill Ave., east side, at the head of Fort Charles Place, showing a general view northward across an excavation for a new apartment house. Shown on Broadway are the elevated tracks of the west side I.R.T. subway. All structures seen across same are in the Bronx; those on the left being in Marble Hill, Manhattan. On the extreme left is a 2½-story frame house (No. 86 Marble Hill Ave.) while north of same and fronting on the same avenue is St. Stephens M.E. Church. This is a set of three views; No. 2 showing a close-up of the new apartment site and No. three, the same area in an eastward direction from Broadway and West 230th Street, in the Bronx.

October 27, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

original_title: Manhattan: Fort Charles Place - Marble Hill Avenue
text:
Fort Charles Place, north to Marble Hill Avenue, showing the repaving of this residential street by the Works Progress Administration. Beyond the trucks appear apartments on the far side of Marble Hill Avenue.

May 3, 1937
1-2-3

W. P. A., photo
Five Boroughs Project
